What really scared me, though, was what Grant would do when we reached Level 3. He’d lie down, destroy his screen, and start playing an old video clip of himself laughing maniacally as he rambled on, slowly eating his computer. Then, without warning, he’d start screaming again, this time in a fit of rage, and stomp down, stomping and stomping and stomping until his head slammed into the wall, shining silver everywhere. Then it was quiet, and for a second I was sure we were going to encounter another security issue. But instead, he just sat there, comfortable in his own skin as he rummaged in the corner of the tiny metal box.

